Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, remove the @Butter{20%g} from your fridge. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{4}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @Coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Trim the @Green Beans{150%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, add the butter, half the garlic and half the coriander. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mash with the back of a #fork{}. Set aside.

Pop your green beans onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Mustard Seeds{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss the coat. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When the beans are halfway through cooking, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Pat the @Monkfish Medallions{200%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once hot, add the monkfish pieces to the pan. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} each side, adjusting the heat as necessary. When cooked, transfer the monkfish pieces to a #bowl{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Add the @Pasanda Style Seasoning{1%sachet} and the remaining garlic to the (now empty) #frying pan{}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Tomato Puree{30%g} into the frying pan. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Coconut Milk{180%ml}, @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the monkfish pieces back into the frying pan. Stir in the @Mango Chutney{40%g}. Warm until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @Plain Naans{2} onto a baking tray. Sprinkle with a little @water{} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once warmed, spread the flavoured butter over the naans.

Share the rice, monkfish curry and green beans between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the remaining coriander.

Serve with the coriander and garlic butter naan bread on the side. Enjoy!